    "encrypted": "false",
    "long_instructions": "A construction company uses a project management app to keep track of construction tasks, and they need to identify **pairs** of consecutive tasks that have not been started yet.\r\n\r\n**✅ TO DO #1:** In the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black;\">Construction</code> class, write the method <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black;\">findIncompletePairs()</code> to return an <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black;\">ArrayList</code> containing pairs of consecutive tasks that are not started.\r\n\r\n- Traverse the <code>tasks</code> list, accessing consecutive pairs of elements.\r\n- If both tasks in the pair have not been started, add both to the returned list.\r\n\r\n**✅ TO DO #2:** In the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black;\">ConstructionRunner</code> class, call the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black;\">findIncompletePairs()</code> method and print the result using the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black;\">tasksToString()</code> method.\r\n\r\n\r\n<details style=\"background-color: #ececec; padding: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px; border: 1px solid transparent; border-radius: 5px;\">\r\n    <summary style=\"font-size: 1.2em; font-weight: bold;\">🔦 Need help with your algorithm?</summary>\r\n    <div style=\"margin-top: 20px; margin-left: 20px; margin-right: 20px;\">\r\n    \t<p>Here is one approach to solving this problem.</p>\r\n        <pre style=\"background-color: #333333; color: white;\">\r\nnew incompletePairs ArrayList\r\nfor each task:\r\n\tfirst = tasks.get(index)\r\n    second = tasks.get(index+1)\r\n    if(!first.hasBeenStarted() && !second.hasBeenStarted()){\r\n    \tincompletePairs.add(first)\r\n        incompletePairs.add(second)\r\n    }\r\nreturn incompletePairs\r\n</pre>\r\n    </div>\r\n</details>",
